1
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:06,633
Is that my hair? All of this?

2
00:00:06,767 --> 00:00:10,000
We will still find
a donor for your treatment.

3
00:00:10,133 --> 00:00:12,033
Their tests are still negative.

4
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:16,433
We will widen our search,
but there is time pressure.

5
00:00:16,567 --> 00:00:18,133
I am not leaving!

6
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:23,333
If Regina has secrets to expose,
I have twice as many.

7
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:25,733
So do not challenge me.

8
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:30,633
Even just this once,
please grant my one request.

9
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:19,167
Sis, thank you

10
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:23,100
for letting Jobert and Mom
stay with you for now.

11
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,933
Of course, Sis.

12
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:28,833
I prefer to have someone at
home.

13
00:01:28,967 --> 00:01:30,533
And I miss Jobert too.

14
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:32,433
It is good that he
can finally leave the hospital.

15
00:01:32,567 --> 00:01:34,300
Marj.

16
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,567
Mom.

17
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,233
Jobert and I are ready.

18
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:44,000
The doctor already signed
the discharge papers.

19
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,633
That is good, Mom.

20
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:51,267
Marj,

21
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:56,233
I mentioned to Jobert
that I want to get tested.

22
00:01:56,367 --> 00:02:01,733
In case I could donate
for Jasmine.

23
00:02:01,867 --> 00:02:06,000
Jobert also mentioned
that he wants to get tested.

24
00:02:06,133 --> 00:02:07,900
Me too, Sis. I am willing.

25
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:12,433
It is touching.

26
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:17,067
I really appreciate
your willingness to get tested.

27
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:19,467
Thank you.

28
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,233
Of course, my child.

29
00:02:21,367 --> 00:02:26,067
[Speaking in Visayan]

30
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:29,967
[Speaking in Visayan]

31
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,433
[Speaking in Visayan]

32
00:02:32,567 --> 00:02:36,733
I will pray, Mom,
that one of you matches.

33
00:02:36,867 --> 00:02:40,667
But it is such a pity.
I wish Jasmine had a sibling.

34
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:44,833
Because that would make
it easier for her, right?

35
00:02:44,967 --> 00:02:46,433
There...

36
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:49,267
would be a higher chance
of a match.

37
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:58,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC]

38
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:10,133
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

39
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:17,000
Ash.

40
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,067
What are you doing here?

41
00:03:22,467 --> 00:03:23,867
I went to your new house.

42
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,800
Ms. Cheche said you came here
to visit Jasmine.

43
00:03:26,933 --> 00:03:29,000
So I figured I would join you.

44
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:30,300
Let us go?

45
00:03:32,167 --> 00:03:35,167
I do not think this is the best
time for you to visit, Xander.

46
00:03:36,733 --> 00:03:38,400
You should just go home.

47
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:40,667
Wait. Where are you going?

48
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:44,900
I am going home.

49
00:03:45,033 --> 00:03:49,167
And for Jasmine's sake,
I suggest you do the same.

50
00:03:51,267 --> 00:03:52,500
Is anything wrong?

51
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,433
Did I do something wrong?

52
00:03:56,633 --> 00:03:57,867
Yes.

53
00:03:58,933 --> 00:04:00,567
Actually, you did.

54
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:02,933
What? What did I do?

55
00:04:03,067 --> 00:04:04,033
Tell me.

56
00:04:05,033 --> 00:04:08,600
You know, I wish you had not
told me you admired me.

57
00:04:08,733 --> 00:04:10,800
I was just telling the truth.

58
00:04:10,933 --> 00:04:13,333
And we both know
Jasmine likes you.

59
00:04:14,467 --> 00:04:16,033
And now she is mad at me.

60
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:20,533
Because she saw and heard us.

61
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,667
And she thinks
I stole you from her.

62
00:04:26,067 --> 00:04:28,667
I do not want to hurt
her anymore, Xander.

63
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:30,867
Just by hanging out with you,
I do not want to.

64
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:36,100
I know this is insensitive,

65
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:38,633
but I will not lie.

66
00:04:38,767 --> 00:04:39,900
I like you.

67
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:42,933
Why me?

68
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:45,767
Why me?

69
00:04:46,667 --> 00:04:48,800
Jas is prettier than me.

70
00:04:48,933 --> 00:04:51,733
You have known each other
longer, right?

71
00:04:51,867 --> 00:04:54,333
And you like her first.

72
00:04:54,467 --> 00:04:56,400
So why can you not just like her
again?

73
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:59,533
Are you serious?
It does not work like that, Ash.

74
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,200
Then try harder.

75
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:11,333
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

76
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:15,867
Is that...

77
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:18,333
Is that your hair?

78
00:05:18,467 --> 00:05:20,133
All of this?

79
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,667
Oh my god, it is happening.

80
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,767
I am losing my hair.

81
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:28,233
They already stopped
the treatment, right?

82
00:05:28,367 --> 00:05:31,567
Why is this still happening?

83
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:34,533
My child,
remember what the doctor said.

84
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,800
Everything is going to be okay.

85
00:05:35,933 --> 00:05:38,833
We will find a donor.

86
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:41,433
How can you be so sure?

87
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:46,033
It feels like the universe
does not want me to get better.

88
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:51,300
Forget your feelings for me.

89
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:56,100
From now on,
stop texting or calling me.

90
00:05:56,233 --> 00:05:58,633
Do not come to the house either.

91
00:05:58,767 --> 00:06:02,000
Let us avoid each other, Xander.

92
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:07,833
Ash!

93
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,300
Ash, wait!

94
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:12,500
It feels like
I am being punished.

95
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:17,000
Why is this happening to me?
I am a good girl.

96
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:21,900
I follow all the schedules
and medications.

97
00:06:22,033 --> 00:06:24,400
I did not spend
my childhood doing normal stuff,

98
00:06:24,533 --> 00:06:26,633
because I wanted to get better.

99
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:28,933
But I am still not
getting better.

100
00:06:29,067 --> 00:06:32,267
Jas, my child, listen to me.

101
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,067
You will get better.

102
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,833
I will do everything
so you can get better.

103
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:39,100
Please.

104
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:50,733
[THEME SONG PLAYING]

105
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:56,100
Your family members have given
me their consent,

106
00:06:56,233 --> 00:06:59,567
that the results
will be given to you directly.

107
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,600
I am so sorry...

108
00:07:02,733 --> 00:07:04,733
Their tests are still negative.

109
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,300
No one has matched yet.

110
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:17,933
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

111
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:19,867
I will give you some time alone.

112
00:07:32,967 --> 00:07:35,167
I do not know
what to do anymore.

113
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:41,233
Jasmine's heart
is already breaking.

114
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,867
What if she finds out the truth?

115
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,467
That there's not a match donor
for her.

116
00:07:48,567 --> 00:07:50,900
What matters is that...

117
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:52,667
she is not giving up.

118
00:07:54,233 --> 00:07:56,567
And she needs to feel that...

119
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,800
we are not giving up either.

120
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:04,933
Please...

121
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:08,000
don't call me "Love".

122
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:12,833
It makes me sick.

123
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:27,433
Are you joking?

124
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:30,467
You want me to take back my
decision for firing you?

125
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,933
Greg...

126
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:36,033
I know I was wrong
for telling Regina.

127
00:08:36,167 --> 00:08:38,200
But can you blame me?

128
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:45,900
Do you think I will tolerate all
your wrong doings?

129
00:08:46,933 --> 00:08:49,100
Our agreement is clear.

130
00:08:49,233 --> 00:08:51,033
I'm not going to go back on my
word.

131
00:08:52,867 --> 00:08:55,333
You're still lucky I didn't drag
you out.

132
00:08:56,500 --> 00:09:02,400
We still gave you enough time to
find a new job.

133
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,500
At my age...

134
00:09:05,633 --> 00:09:08,233
You think I can start a new job?

135
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:10,967
I've served this family
for decades...

136
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:12,700
to you Greg.

137
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:15,000
Your family serves as my home.

138
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:18,533
Weng, Cheche, Oscar.

139
00:09:19,567 --> 00:09:23,800
Serving you is the only thing I
know how to do.

140
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:25,067
Then...

141
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:28,267
Find a new thing
that you want to do.

142
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:31,733
Don't think of this
as getting fired.

143
00:09:31,867 --> 00:09:34,233
Think of this
as your retirement.

144
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:37,067
I'll add onto
your separation pay.

145
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:40,200
I am not leaving.

146
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:42,067
Do not force me, Greg.

147
00:09:43,067 --> 00:09:46,333
If not, I will expose
the dirty secrets I know...

148
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:48,500
Most especially about you!

149
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,467
Are you threatening me?

150
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:56,033
Yes.

151
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:57,933
I am serious...

152
00:09:58,067 --> 00:09:59,800
Sir Greg.

153
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:03,767
I will not leave,
and I do not want to leave.

154
00:10:03,933 --> 00:10:05,867
I don't want to be apart.

155
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:10,167
If Regina knows a lot of
secrets,

156
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,533
I have a lot more in my pocket.

157
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:15,700
So, don't test me.

158
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:21,000
Now what?

159
00:10:21,133 --> 00:10:22,900
Will you still fire me?

160
00:10:23,867 --> 00:10:27,033
Or you will allow me to stay?

161
00:10:50,767 --> 00:10:52,667
How are you?

162
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:55,133
You did not go home, did you?

163
00:10:55,267 --> 00:10:56,633
Why would I go back there?

164
00:10:56,767 --> 00:10:58,867
My child is here
in the hospital.

165
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,400
I understand.

166
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,133
Mr. and Mrs. Torrecampo.

167
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:08,967
I just want to update you

168
00:11:09,133 --> 00:11:11,433
that since there
is still no match for Jasmine,

169
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:12,667
what we can do

170
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:16,200
is make sure she remains stable
and free from infection.

171
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:19,600
But there is time pressure.

172
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,233
What do you mean?

173
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,433
Doctor, I read something.

174
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:30,933
If it takes too long to find
a donor for Jasmine

175
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:34,133
and her condition weakens,

176
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:36,633
she might no longer be eligible
for a transplant

177
00:11:36,767 --> 00:11:38,667
once a donor is found?

178
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,467
What does this mean?

179
00:11:42,667 --> 00:11:45,767
Please, do not lose hope,
Mrs. Torrecampo.

180
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:48,633
We will widen our search
for potential donors,

181
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:50,233
and if necessary,

182
00:11:50,367 --> 00:11:52,467
I will update the donor registry
every day,

183
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:55,733
I will do that
so we can get through this.

184
00:11:55,867 --> 00:12:05,833
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

185
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:11,433
<i> My God,</i>

186
00:12:11,567 --> 00:12:16,833
<i>I know You do not give trials
I cannot endure.</i>

187
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,700
<i>I accepted every blow
and hardship You gave me</i>

188
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:23,233
<i> all my life.</i>

189
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:27,467
<i>I never got angry or stopped
believing in You.</i>

190
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:33,667
<i> [Speaking in Visayan]</i>

191
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:37,333
<i> But please,</i>

192
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:39,800
<i> allow me to breathe.</i>

193
00:12:39,933 --> 00:12:41,567
<i> Even just for now.</i>

194
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:46,067
<i>Please, grant
my one request.</i>

195
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:52,500
<i>I hope we find a donor
soon so Jasmine can recover.</i>

196
00:12:52,667 --> 00:12:55,600
<i> I cannot bear losing my child.</i>

197
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,667
<i> I love my child very much.</i>

198
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:09,400
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

199
00:13:09,533 --> 00:13:12,767
What if we cannot find a donor
for Jasmine?

200
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:14,567
That is so sad.

201
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:17,533
Not a single one
in their family matched.

202
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:19,900
Even we did not match.

203
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:21,633
Poor Jasmine.

204
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,667
There will surely be one.

205
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:28,567
I am sure if it were possible to
ask every family in the world,

206
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,067
they would do it.

207
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,067
There is still hope.

208
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,133
Oh dear.

209
00:13:33,267 --> 00:13:38,667
I do not think we need
to test the whole world.

210
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,933
In this very house,

211
00:13:41,067 --> 00:13:43,267
there is one person who has not
yet been checked

212
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,100
as a match for Jasmine.

213
00:13:45,233 --> 00:13:55,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

214
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,367
You are still here?

215
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:21,200
I thought only your eyes
were poor?

216
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:25,033
Turns out your ears and brain
need a checkup too.

217
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:28,733
I will give you spectacles
for your poor comprehension

218
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:30,200
so things are clearer for you.

219
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:32,067
You are fired.
You are dismissed.

220
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,967
Get out!

221
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:36,300
Sorry, Ma'am Regina.

222
00:14:36,433 --> 00:14:41,033
My understanding is that Sir has
the final say in this house.

223
00:14:41,167 --> 00:14:43,533
He said I am not dismissed.

224
00:14:43,667 --> 00:14:45,167
So I am not leaving.

225
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:46,367
What?

226
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,433
Please ask Sir instead.

227
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:58,533
[INTENSE MUSIC]

228
00:15:00,367 --> 00:15:02,700
You totally undermined me, Greg!

229
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:06,367
You did not even talk to me
about that decision.

230
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,967
I thought you would be happy
since Yolly is your eyes here.

231
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,967
So now you have someone
watching me again.

232
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,200
Not anymore.

233
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:15,567
Ever since I found out
what she says behind our backs.

234
00:15:16,733 --> 00:15:20,400
They are the help. Of course
they talk about their employers.

235
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,767
That is nothing new.

236
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,867
Oh, my dear foolish husband,

237
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,967
do you not know
that woman basks in our misery?

238
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:31,433
She enjoys seeing us
fall apart and suffer.

239
00:15:31,567 --> 00:15:33,233
And that is verbatim.

240
00:15:33,367 --> 00:15:34,500
Really, Regina?

241
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:38,067
We just lost our
precious mansion.

242
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:42,300
Our child and the in-law
are engaging in infidelity,

243
00:15:42,433 --> 00:15:43,533
and worse,

244
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:48,400
one of our grandchildren is
losing hair because of cancer.

245
00:15:49,367 --> 00:15:50,933
People are dying, Regina.

246
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:55,033
Are we really going to fight
over an old woman

247
00:15:55,167 --> 00:15:57,633
who has been a great help
to our family?

248
00:15:57,767 --> 00:16:00,300
I am only asking for respect,
Greg.

249
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:01,733
What I do not understand

250
00:16:01,867 --> 00:16:03,833
is why you suddenly changed
your mind

251
00:16:03,967 --> 00:16:07,033
when we decided to let her go.

252
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:08,033
Are you not afraid

253
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:10,933
that she might be consorting
with her coven

254
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:15,500
and gave you some potion
recipe to change your mind?

255
00:16:18,167 --> 00:16:21,000
My decision is final, Regina.

256
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:23,933
You still have not answered
my question.

257
00:16:24,067 --> 00:16:28,467
What does that woman have on you
that you cannot let her go?

258
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,067
Like I said,

259
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,667
she is a great help to us

260
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:35,900
and we cannot afford to lose
people right now.

261
00:16:36,033 --> 00:16:38,333
And this
conversation is over.

262
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:39,500
No!

263
00:16:39,633 --> 00:16:43,167
It is over when
I say it is over!

264
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:53,100
[INTENSE MUSIC]

265
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:54,900
Look,

266
00:16:55,033 --> 00:16:56,367
just because you sometimes
get your way

267
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:58,467
with your cursed demands,

268
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:01,267
does not mean you can abuse
my kindness.

269
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:07,767
You think you now have
power over me to dictate to me?

270
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:09,800
You are mistaken, Regina.

271
00:17:09,933 --> 00:17:11,533
I am only indulging you.

272
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:18,533
You are, and you will always be,
just a trophy spouse.

273
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:23,967
You are just an accessory
when I face others.

274
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:26,933
A shiny doll
in front of the camera

275
00:17:27,067 --> 00:17:30,067
to prove to everyone
we are perfect.

276
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:33,600
That we are better than
them despite the problems.

277
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:36,833
That is all it
will ever be.

278
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:41,267
Because...

279
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:47,000
I no longer have even a shred of
feeling left for you.

280
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:48,233
[CLATTERS]

281
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:54,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

282
00:17:58,933 --> 00:18:08,900
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

283
00:18:15,267 --> 00:18:17,533
I said, get that away from me!
I do not want that!

284
00:18:17,667 --> 00:18:19,967
I do not want to drink it!
Just get out!

285
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:22,400
I will handle this. Thank you.

286
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:25,567
Jasmine, what is wrong?

287
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:27,967
Why do you not want
to take your medicine?

288
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:30,167
What are my meds even for, Mom?

289
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:32,400
They cannot even find a donor
for me.

290
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:34,033
So I am not going
to get better anyway.

291
00:18:34,167 --> 00:18:35,733
I am just going to die.

292
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:39,133
So what, you are giving up?

293
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:42,000
When all of us
are doing everything for you?

294
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:44,300
But I did not ask you to.

295
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:46,000
So that is it?

296
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:49,133
Like you are saying our
sacrifices mean nothing?

297
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:52,233
Are you okay with dying?

298
00:18:52,367 --> 00:18:53,967
Well, I am not!

299
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:57,200
Can you not see?

300
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:00,567
We are more than ready
to fight for you.

301
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,667
My child,
so I hope you fight too.

302
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:05,333
We will never give up.

303
00:19:05,467 --> 00:19:07,767
Jasmine,
we are doing everything

304
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:11,033
because we love you so much.

305
00:19:11,167 --> 00:19:13,967
So please,
do not give up on yourself.

306
00:19:15,867 --> 00:19:17,900
I am just so tired, Mom.

307
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:22,567
It is hard
not to want to give up.

308
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,367
I know.

309
00:19:25,433 --> 00:19:27,867
I know, my child.
I understand you.

310
00:19:28,867 --> 00:19:30,467
But I want you to fight.

311
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:34,700
I want you to be brave, okay?

312
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:36,733
So please,

313
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:38,500
do not leave us.

314
00:19:39,767 --> 00:19:41,967
Do not give up on us.

315
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:43,167
Okay?

316
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:53,067
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

317
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,100
Stop crying now, okay?

318
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:58,433
- That is enough.
- Sorry, Mom.

319
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:00,000
Sorry.

320
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:09,000
Carrying the tea looks
like a team effort

321
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,567
when I only asked you, Yolly.

322
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:14,767
Ma'am, I was just helping Miss.

323
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:16,933
She might trip.

324
00:20:17,067 --> 00:20:19,333
You know, her eyesight is poor.

325
00:20:19,467 --> 00:20:22,133
And she is not familiar
with the house yet.

326
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:24,200
Am I talking to you?

327
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:27,200
- Leave.
- It is okay. I am fine.

328
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:29,400
Go back to the kitchen.
Give that to me.

329
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,100
Go on.

330
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:37,733
Be careful with that, okay?
That is an antique.

331
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:40,300
That is more precious
than your entire family.

332
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:47,633
What is this?

333
00:20:47,767 --> 00:20:49,133
I did not mean it, Ma'am.

334
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:51,267
What do you mean
you did not mean it?

335
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,800
What do you mean
you did not mean it?

336
00:20:52,933 --> 00:20:54,767
Maybe you are really getting
back at me

337
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:57,500
because you know
I want you out of here.

338
00:20:57,633 --> 00:20:59,633
- No, Ma'am. No.
- Huh, look at this.

339
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:02,100
You know what, let us
just call it even, right?

340
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:04,667
- [CLAMORING]
- [EXCLAIMS]

341
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:09,433
[INTENSE MUSIC]

342
00:21:10,167 --> 00:21:12,500
That was an antique.
What is wrong with you, Marj?

343
00:21:12,633 --> 00:21:14,000
- Do not interfere!
- Mom.

344
00:21:14,133 --> 00:21:15,767
You are worried
about an antique?

345
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:18,933
You were already about to claw
Ms. Yolly's face.

346
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:22,167
She splashed me first.

347
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:24,000
I was just returning the favor.

348
00:21:24,133 --> 00:21:26,233
I did not mean to, Ma'am.

349
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:27,833
It was an accident!

350
00:21:27,967 --> 00:21:29,233
Stop lying!

351
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:32,000
Mom, enough!

352
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:34,133
If you do not stop attacking
Ms. Yolly,

353
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:36,133
I will be forced
to stand up to you.

354
00:21:36,267 --> 00:21:40,800
[INTENSE MUSIC]

355
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:43,000
You want to stay here?

356
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:45,300
Then suffer through it!

357
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:48,200
And you, wait until Paolo hears
about this.

358
00:21:48,333 --> 00:21:58,300
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

359
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:08,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

360
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:14,633
Are you okay?

361
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,167
I am okay.

362
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:18,267
Thank you.

363
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:21,367
Miss, are you sure you did
not get burned on your face?

364
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:27,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

365
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:30,533
You really are different
from this family.

366
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:36,533
You are a good child.

367
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:39,933
I just do not understand
why God keeps testing you

368
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:43,000
with so many trials.

369
00:22:44,267 --> 00:22:46,900
Thank you for
defending me earlier.

370
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:50,700
Tell me, Marj.

371
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:52,967
Maybe I can do something...

372
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:55,633
to repay the kindness
you gave me.

373
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:03,233
Maybe you can still find
a donor for my child.

374
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:07,567
I am not asking for anything
in return.

375
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:16,133
Our whole family and even
my friends have been tested,

376
00:23:16,267 --> 00:23:17,867
but no one has matched.

377
00:23:19,733 --> 00:23:22,533
My child is running
out of time, Ms. Yolly.

378
00:23:24,233 --> 00:23:26,533
If this goes on without a donor,

379
00:23:27,733 --> 00:23:29,600
there is a chance
she will not recover.

380
00:23:31,433 --> 00:23:34,300
She could die,
and we would be helpless.

381
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:39,400
There is still
hope, Ma'am Marj.

382
00:23:41,167 --> 00:23:51,133
[INTENSEM MUSIC]

383
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:59,733
[INTENSE MUSIC]

384
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:11,767
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

385
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:15,267
What is this?

386
00:25:16,767 --> 00:25:26,733
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

387
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:14,200
There is still hope, Ma'am Marj.

388
00:26:14,333 --> 00:26:16,533
There is one more person close
to you who could be a donor.

389
00:26:16,667 --> 00:26:18,567
You just need to know the truth.

390
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:28,467
[INTENSE MUSIC]

391
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:30,700
Have they still not found
a donor?

392
00:26:30,833 --> 00:26:31,833
Still none, Mom.

393
00:26:31,967 --> 00:26:33,767
Several days have already
passed.

394
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:36,033
My child is losing hope.

395
00:26:36,167 --> 00:26:39,033
Even I am breaking
from fear and worry.

396
00:26:39,167 --> 00:26:40,833
It looks like you are going
through something heavy.

397
00:26:40,967 --> 00:26:45,200
Oh dear, you know, maybe Greg
should have been a magician.

398
00:26:45,367 --> 00:26:48,000
Maybe he could make me
disappear or cut me in half.

399
00:26:48,133 --> 00:26:50,733
Do not let him destroy
your self-esteem.

400
00:26:50,867 --> 00:26:53,867
Be like the woman my father
always tells me about.

401
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:57,000
A strong woman who would
never let herself be outplayed.

402
00:26:57,133 --> 00:26:59,067
Someone who knows
their self-worth.

403
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:01,100
I wanted to talk to you.

404
00:27:01,233 --> 00:27:03,233
You need to know the truth.

405
00:27:03,367 --> 00:27:04,933
What truth?

406
00:27:05,067 --> 00:27:10,833
If Greg will not remove
the house help, I will.

407
00:27:10,967 --> 00:27:15,667
Is that not the hoodie Marj said
the arsonist was wearing?

408
00:27:15,833 --> 00:27:20,067
[INTENSE MUSIC]
